You cannot indent or outdent the project summary task. The "Standard" calendar is the default calendar for the project, and is the basis for resource calendars. This calendar reflects a traditional work schedule: Monday through Friday, from 8:00 A.M. to 5:00 P.M., with an hour off for break. All time, from Sunday through Saturday, from 12:00 A.M. to 12:00 A.M., is set as working time. The "24 Hours" calendar reflects a schedule with no nonworking time at all. The "24 Hours" calendar can be used when resources and tasks are scheduled for different shifts around the clock, or when equipment resources work on tasks continuously. The "Night Shift" calendar reflects a graveyard shift schedule of Monday night through Saturday morning, 11:00 P.M. to 8:00 A.M., with 3:00 A.M. to 4:00 A.M. designated as nonworking time for break.
